Gauteng Premier David Makhura says interventions implemented in the fight against COVID-19 in the province are working. He says there are still concerns about the increase of confirmed cases in the Johannesburg CBD. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura says interventions implemented in the fight against COVID-19 in the province are working. Makhura was giving an update on the status of the fight against the spread of the coronavirus in the province. The province has over 7,000 COVID-19 infections with 57 deaths. Gauteng's recoveries stand at 2,825. WATCH: Gauteng gives update on COVID-19 He says there are still concerns about the increase of confirmed cases in the Johannesburg CBD. “In the CBD of Johannesburg, we have the largest number of cases,” said Makhura. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.